definitions.example: There has been a cutback in federal subsidies. Too, rates have been increasing.

definitions.definition: (degree) To an excessive degree; over; more than enough.

definitions.example: She doesn't talk too much.  I'm not too sure about this.

definitions.definition: (affirmation) Used to contradict a negative assertion.
definitions.example: "You're not old enough yet."  "I am, too!"
